<DIV type=1>

<HEAD>
You will find out more about your injections in the inside of this leaflet
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Your injection is  called 
<EMPH weight="bold">
Miacalcic
</EMPH>
. Injections of 
<EMPH weight="bold">
Miacalcic
</EMPH>
 are given to reduce the amount of calcium in your blood, which may be raised in various illnesses, including for example Paget’s disease of bone. 
<EMPH weight="bold">
Miacalcic
</EMPH>
 is also given in disorders of bone, where calcium levels need altering.
</BLOCK>


