<HEAD weight="bold" >
Storing your injections
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Store the injections in a fridge.
</BLOCK>


</DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV type=1>

<HEAD>
If you DO NOT use a whole 50 IU or 100 IU ampoule
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Once in use, the 400 IU multidose vials may be stored at room temperature for up to one month. You must throw away any remainder if you have not used it within a month.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Keep your medicine in a safe place where children cannot reach it. Your medicine could harm them.
</BLOCK>

<CB n=2>

<BLOCK>
If your doctor decides to stop your treatment, return any leftover medicine to the pharmacist. Only keep it if your doctor tells you to.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
DO NOT give your medicine to anyone else.
</BLOCK>

